irst systematic study of policy analysis activities in Spain. It provides a comprehensive overview of how policy actors, including politicians, think tanks, researchers, interest groups and experts, generate information for the policy-making process. The book explores how executive and legislative actors participate in the production of policy analysis and how all actors elaborate and disseminate information on policy analysis. Contributors consider the ways different policy actors are involved in the production of data and information about policy problems, the resources used to produce policy analysis and the type of analysis produced over time in different policy areas.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aPolicy scienceszSpain. 0aPolitical sciencezSpain. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aAlarcón, Pau, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAubanell-Jubany, Anna Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBacaria, Jordi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarberà, Oscar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarreras, Albert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCasal, Fernando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCerrillo, Ivan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaqués-Bonafont, Laura , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChaqués-Bonafont, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCosta, Oriol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFont, Joan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGeva-May, Iris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/